 surrounded by terms of other benefits that farmers can easily perceive. Other benefits referred to by the people who responded 
 were the ease of land preparation as alleys become 
 flatter (5%), hedgerow species serving as food (8%), 
 and the avoidance of physical damage to crops due to 
 gully (creation and construction/ group of objects) and landslide (4%). These other benefits, however, tend to be somewhat location specific. 
