 major problem. 
 Most non-adopters have taken measures 
 to reduce the soil wearing away on their fields, of which 
 23% have built diversion/drainage narrow waterways, another 23% have practiced outline plowing, and about 
 16% have responded simply by using more (material that makes plants grow better). 
 Unplanteding the land and placing other physical (blocking things) are the other wearing away-reducing measures practiced 
 by 12% of the farmers. These responses point to/show that 
