 4.6. Returns to adoption 
 Data problems attacked a truly energetic cost-benefit 
 analysis of investment in outline hedgerows. Two 
 major relationships are needed/demanded. The first is the 
 relationship between wearing away (or soil depth) and working well. The second is the relationship between (protecting something from harm) measure and soil wearing away. The time path of 
 land working well with wearing away control measure can be 
 (described the future) by combining these two relationships. Con- 
 
 siderable investments in research efforts have been 
 made to understand the nature of these relationships, 
 as well as to develop (testing out) models to (describe the future) the 
 effect of soil (protecting something from harm) practices on working well. 
 Although a few models with different degrees of 
 sophistication are now available (Young and Muraya, 
 1990; McCown et al., 1995), the professional is held back by the fact that the adjustment and validation 
 of these models often require (large/relatively large) data and, 
 sometimes, the redoing/redesigning of some of the relationships. 
 Given the (problems, delays, etc.) talked about/said above, a somewhat 
 simpler approach of depending on sensitivity analysis to 
 highlight the major factors that decide/figure out the money-making ability of investment in soil wearing away control is begun/tried instead of conducting a real cost-benefit 
 analysis. Time-related patterns of changes in yield from 
 fields with and without outline hedgerows are ignored 
 in this approach and, instead, yield is assumed to remain constant over time at their (pertaining to each person or thing) levels in 
 both situations. The average cost of beginning and building on outline hedgerows (49 mandays), the average once-a-year cost 
 of maintenance (14 mandays), and the (fair in amount, related to something else/properly sized compared to something else) 
 area lost to hedgerows (20%) are received/got from the 
 survey data (Table 7). The percentage increase in yield 
 of maize needed/demanded to recover these costs at different discount rates are calculated assuming the life of outline 
 hedgerows to be 10 years 7 . As adoption of outline 
